<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/414383-buying-watermelon-candy-in-the-early-30-s">Buying watermelon candy in the early 30&#39;s? That came out in the late 70&#39;s. Eye makeup dripping down her face? Stick mascara did not come out until the 60&#39;s. A young writer needs to have the manuscript read by an older person or a person who knows details of social history to prevent these mistakes that take away the honesty of the book.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_414383'><a id="like_count_community_question_414383" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/414383?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15818107-orphan-train">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/414383-buying-watermelon-candy-in-the-early-30-s">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/414383-buying-watermelon-candy-in-the-early-30-s">See all 6 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6505452-alicia-boyle"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1317407753i/6505452._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6505452-alicia-boyle">Alicia Boyle</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Mascara was around during the great depression and it had a habit of running down ones face. Here&apos;s an ad.<br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://en.paperblog.com/maybelline-cousins1934-during-the-great-depression-1242326/'>http://en.paperblog.com/maybelline-co...</a><br/>Wate<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Mascara was around during the great depression and it had a habit of running down ones face. Here's an ad.<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://en.paperblog.com/maybelline-cousins1934-during-the-great-depression-1242326/">http://en.paperblog.com/maybelline-co...</a><br />Watermelon candy was available during the depression era. You can read about watermelon candy in other books about the depression. In the book "Voices of the Great Depression--The 1930's"by Cinda Anderson on page 14 the write mentions watermelon candy. I think it my have been an off shoot of the Turkish delight/orange fruit slices type candy.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
